  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Responding to Food Insecurity in South Sudan through Water, Sanitation, and Hygiene (WASH) Frontline and Pipeline</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Over the last 12 months, South Sudan has experienced recurring floods, which have negatively impacted the population, causing massive displacement, and leading to the destruction of crops and property. Good access to water, sanitation and hygiene services (WASH) is critical in such contexts as it helps secure nutritional outcomes, since unclean water, inadequate sanitation and poor hygiene practices are directly linked to undernutrition. However, WASH coverage across some of these counties has decreased over the years. This project targets beneficiaries in the three targeted counties (Tonj North, Tonj South and Tonj East) and contributes to provide life-saving assistance against food insecurity by addressing the most acute WASH needs whilst increasing access to safe, equitable and dignified access to WASH services.</narrative>
  </description>
